pageContext.claim: “And also, Greg Murphy -- which nobody is even reporting -- but Greg Murphy won a great congressional election in North Carolina last night. And I want to congratulate, between Dan and Greg, what a job they did. We picked up two seats [including Dan Bishop's election], and Greg was, you know, anticipated to win by two or three points, maybe less, but two or three points.”
pageContext.analysis: Republicans already held both seats, so it's false to say "we picked up two seats." Murphy was widely expected to win, and no forecast had him as close to his opponent as Trump falsely claims. His victory was widely reported, contrary to Trump's claim.
